{
  "texts": [
    "In this regime, the effective spin degrees of freedom -relevant in the lowenergy infrared limit -depart from those in the microscopic model (Eq.",
    "( 1)), instead taking values that are odd multiples of π/q.",
    "This emergence of forbidden degrees of freedom in the infrared limit, induced by competing interactions, is a central result of this work.",
    "We refer to this phase as the Z - q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM [83] phase.",
    "We confirm this emergent behavior by computing the staggered magnetization on one of the √ 2 × √ 2 sublattices for each CMC snapshot:m = 1 L 2 /2 ix,iy (-1) ix+iy exp(iθ (ix,iy)),(3)where i x(y) runs over the rotated sublattice and L is the linear size of the system."
  ]
}